427.5: Cardiac arrest:
ChatCompletionMessage(content='- Sudden and unexpected cessation of heart function
- Loss of blood circulation
- Rapid loss of consciousness
- Abnormal or absent breathing
- No detectable pulse
- Irregular heart rhythm (arrhythmia), often ventricular fibrillation or ventricular tachycardia
- Collapse and unresponsiveness
- Potential for coma due to prolonged oxygen deprivation to the brain
- Near-death experiences in some survivors

Note: The text does not provide a comprehensive list of signs and symptoms for everyone experiencing cardiac arrest, as about 50 percent of people have no warning signs. For those with symptoms, they can be nonspecific such as chest pain, fatigue, blackouts, dizziness, shortness of breath, weakness, and vomiting.', role='assistant', function_call=None, tool_calls=None)
285.9: Anemia:
ChatCompletionMessage(content='- Tiredness
- Weakness
- Shortness of breath
- Headaches
- Reduced ability to exercise
- Confusion
- Feeling like one is going to pass out
- Loss of consciousness
- Increased thirst
- Pallor (notably when anemia is significant)
- Dizziness
- Intolerance to physical exertion
- Difficulty concentrating
- Irregular or rapid heartbeat
- Cold hands and feet
- Cold intolerance
- Pale or yellow skin
- Poor appetite
- Easy bruising and bleeding
- Muscle weakness
- Chest pain (when anemia is acute)
- Sweating (when anemia is acute)
- Palpitations
- Angina
- Intermittent claudication of the legs
- Symptoms of heart failure
- Pallor of skin, mucosa, conjunctiva, and nail beds
- Blue coloration of the sclera in some cases of iron-deficiency anemia
- Koilonychia (in iron deficiency)
- Jaundice (in hemolytic anemia)
- Nerve cell damage (in vitamin B12 deficiency)
- Bone deformities (in thalassemia major)
- Leg ulcers (in sickle-cell disease)
- Tachycardia (fast heart rate)
- Bounding pulse
- Flow murmurs
- Cardiac ventricular hypertrophy (enlargement)
- Pica (consumption of non-food items)
- Behavioral disturbances (in children with chronic anemia)
- Restless legs syndrome (more common in iron-deficiency anemia)', role='assistant', function_call=None, tool_calls=None)
